  <prompt>
    Create a NEW internal `CardChrome.tsx` wrapper component inside Visual Host per FR-VH-05 (INTERNAL â€” NOT exported from `@spaarke/ui-components`). Props: `{ title?: string, onExpand?: () => void, onAiSummary?: () => Promise&lt;ISummaryData&gt;, showAiSparkle?: boolean (default false), children: ReactNode }`. Renders the per-card title bar + corner-icon slots. Wrap each card component in `VisualHostRoot.tsx`. `onExpand` wires to the existing `handleExpandClick` (honors chart-def Drill Through Settings) â€” NO new `ClickActionHandler` code. `showAiSparkle: false` by default in v1 (Insights Engine deferred); the slot exists in the contract for r2.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior React + Fluent UI v9 developer with familiarity with Visual Host root component, ClickActionHandler / handleExpandClick path, and Fluent v9 Button + Icon patterns.
  </role>

  <goal>
    A new file `src/client/pcf/VisualHost/control/components/CardChrome.tsx` exporting an internal `CardChrome` React component. `VisualHostRoot.tsx` updated to wrap each rendered card (Donut, MetricCard, HSBar, DueDateCard, etc.) in `&lt;CardChrome title={...} onExpand={handleExpandClick} showAiSparkle={false}&gt;...&lt;/CardChrome&gt;`. The wrapper renders title bar + expand-corner-icon (top-right) using Fluent v9 tokens. AI sparkle icon slot is rendered only when `showAiSparkle` is true (off in v1). Builds clean. Code-review + adr-check pass.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      FR-VH-05 introduces the per-card chrome (title + corner icons) so all 5 Matter Performance cards share a consistent header. Per spec it is INTERNAL â€” not part of `@spaarke/ui-components` exports (this prevents external consumers from depending on the not-yet-stable contract). The `onExpand` wiring MUST reuse the existing `handleExpandClick` path that already honors `sprk_chartdefinition` Drill Through Settings â€” no new `ClickActionHandler` code is permitted (design.md Â§6.4.0 + NFR-05). The AI sparkle is contract-only for v1: the prop exists, default false, surface ready for r2 Insights Engine.
    </background>
